The paper deals with graph isomorphism and automorphisms, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of fixed parameter tractability (FPT) suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves algorithms and data structures for graphs (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG), as well as machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG) in the context of graph isomorphism.
